  "text": "The LLVM optimization pass pipeline lifecycle involves the following key files in the sg-evals/llvm-project--a8f3c97d repository:\n\n1. **PassBuilder class definition** (`llvm/include/llvm/Passes/PassBuilder.h`): Defines the `PassBuilder` class (line 114), which is the main entry point for constructing LLVM optimization pipelines. Its implementation resides in `llvm/lib/Passes/PassBuilder.cpp`, which handles pass registration and pipeline parsing.\n\n2. **PassManager template class** (`llvm/include/llvm/IR/PassManager.h`): Defines the core `PassManager<IRUnitT, AnalysisManagerT, ExtraArgTs...>` template class (line 162) — the fundamental pass execution engine. Convenience typedefs like `ModulePassManager` and `FunctionPassManager` are derived from it.\n\n3. **PassBuilderPipelines** (`llvm/lib/Passes/PassBuilderPipelines.cpp`): Implements the pipeline assembly methods including `PassBuilder::buildPerModuleDefaultPipeline` (the default O2/O3 module pipeline) and `PassBuilder::buildModuleSimplificationPipeline` (core function and module simplification sub-pipeline). This file wires together all the individual passes into coherent optimization sequences.\n\n4. **PassRegistry.def** (`llvm/lib/Passes/PassRegistry.def`): A X-macro definitions file that registers all standard passes (module passes, function passes, loop passes, CGSCC passes, etc.) used by the new pass manager infrastructure.\n\n5. **DeadStoreElimination** (`llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/DeadStoreElimination.cpp`): A concrete example of a scalar optimization pass implementing `DSEPass`, which eliminates stores whose values are never read before being overwritten or before the function exits."
}

